        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/olivia-grant-hugs-grandmother-mary-grace-sileo-plastic-cloth-wantagh-new-york.png" alt="Olivia Grant hugs her grandmother, Mary Grace Sileo, through a plastic cloth hung on a clothesline in Wantagh, New York" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF"> 
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            <i>Olivia Grant hugs her grandmother, Mary Grace Sileo, through a plastic cloth hung on a clothesline in Wantagh, New York. Credits: Al Bello/Getty Images</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
       
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Five years ago, on March 11, 2020, the COVID-19 pandemic was <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-15-03-2025-h1-1-declared-a-global-pandemic?source=website" target="_blank">declared a global pandemic</a>. The pandemic reshaped the world in ways it is still grappling with. When travel restrictions were announced and institutions shut down, life was never the same. Over 7 million lives were lost, and it took a profound mental toll on the masses.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">Young people miss out on significant amounts of school. Misinformation flourished among people of all ages. It fueled vaccine skepticism and deepened societal divisions. The media landscape shifted, with trust eroding amid political attacks and selective truth. While these issues were already ongoing before the pandemic started, the pandemic put them into overdrive.</p>
        </mj-text> 
      </mj-column>
